<p><location_mentioned>Pleasant Fountain</location_mentioned> <date_mentioned n="12-18-1817">Decr. 18th 1817</date_mentioned></p>
<p>Dear Sir you will be so good as to pay to <person_mentioned>Mr Wm Harrison</person_mentioned> forty 
dollars and forty Cents the amount of your and your <person_mentioned>farther</person_mentioned>s account
as he had not the mony when we settled and I owe <person_mentioned>Mr. Harrison</person_mentioned> and
he is a going a way your compliance will much oblige</p>

<p><person_mentioned>Mr. S. F. Austin</person_mentioned>  </p>    

<p><person_mentioned>A. Miller</person_mentioned></p>

<p>N. B. <person_mentioned>Mr Harrison</person_mentioned> has our settlement which you Can see what the
Ballance is due me.</p>

<p><person_mentioned>A. M.</person_mentioned></p>

<p>Recd the within in full <date_mentioned n="12-19-1817">Decb. 19 1817</date_mentioned></p>

